node.text:
Proud to represent such an amazing company and work alongside some even better people! @bushnell_official is a company I’ve used for years, and after hunting with the new Fusion X Rangefinding Bono’s in Alaska and the Prime 1800 rangefinder in Kentucky, the new #Activsync technology is something I can definitely stand behind.
I only work with company’s and products I truly believe in, and Bushnell is one of those. Preciate y’all for listening to our 2 cents on using Activsync in the field!
-
@officialbonecollector @tboneoutdoors @whitetailfreakstv @merlethecorgi_

node.title: Just a couple of Rednecks explaining Bushnell’s Activsync technology 👊🏻

He can’t do much with his left arm, so he’s doing some things to keep busy that won’t put strain on it.
After killing a turkey this year on our place in Kansas using @cody.cutler’s .410, he had to break down and buy one and pattern it using the same shells!

node.text:
-
I promised the video of weighing this fish, and I had a lot of close guesses! But she came in at 40lbs! Here’s a short video of the catch, weighing, and release of this beautiful Blue! The full video, and way more like this are on my YouTube channel! The link is in my bio. When we first checked the hole, we all thought it was flathead in there. I didn’t wear a sleeve because it would have taken forever to find one in the boat, and flatheads don’t bite NEAR as hard as blue cats, and their teeth (like sandpaper) aren’t quiet as sharp. So instead of taking the time to find a sleeve, I found out the hard way that the fish was a blue cat. I absolutely LOVE blue catfish. They’re the pit bulls of the water, and they’ll give you the fight of your life! I’ve never caught one without a sleeve that didn’t draw a lot of blood. They’re definitely worth it though!
-
Scale: @huntingmadeeasy
-

If y’all remember, I had my 2018 Kansas buck carved by @skulls.millworks (watch until the end to see pictures and some examples of what he can do) and now we’re giving him dads 8 point he killed with @buck_chasers in Illinois to carve too! We’ve decided to do a little giveaway for y’all.
-
@skulls.millworks is giving y’all $500 worth of work on a skull of your choice. You can send him one of yours like I did, or he will provide a hog skull for you! He’ll carve it, bronze it, put a rust finish, or whatever you want on it! He’s crazy talented, and he can make a skull look amazing. -
How to enter:
-
1. Follow both me @hannahbarron96 & @skulls.millworks -
2. Comment tagging 2 friends! (Each comment tagging 2 friends counts as an additional entry!)
-
That’s it! The winner will be chosen at random and announced next Wednesday night on my story, so be watching! And make sure to follow all the rules because I will check!
-
Preciate y’all!
-
- *This giveaway is not endorsed by or affiliated with Instagram. By entering you are confirming you are at least 16 years of age, agree to instagrams terms of use, and release Instagram of responsibility..**

node.text:
We’re working on a small scale guide service this year in Fort Scott, Kansas. Me and my dad @jeffbarron70 are partnering with @cody.cutler (the fellah we’ve hunted with in Kansas for the past 3 years and bought our own Kansas land from) to make this happen. To kick it off, we’re raffling off tickets at $25 a piece to win a trip with us. We’re only selling 160 tickets (amounts to $500 less than these hunts cost) and 80 are already gone! So don’t miss out! BUT, if you do miss out, we’ll be running another raffle later if this one goes well. Contact @cody.cutler for details on how to buy a raffle ticket or book a hunt!
-
Preciate y’all!
-
-
Raptor in the background 👀: @paulthigpen

node.text:
Proud to represent such an amazing company and work alongside some even better people! @bushnell_official is a company I’ve used for years, and after hunting with the new Fusion X Rangefinding Bono’s in Alaska and the Prime 1800 rangefinder in Kentucky, the new #Activsync technology is something I can definitely stand behind.
I only work with company’s and products I truly believe in, and Bushnell is one of those. Preciate y’all for listening to our 2 cents on using Activsync in the field!
-
@officialbonecollector @tboneoutdoors @whitetailfreakstv @merlethecorgi_

First Caribou in the books!

node.text:
Shots were fired in Alaska 💥
-
📸: @tydox
Had so much fun with @kristylee15 & @themostwantedlist in Alaska last week! Got to take my first caribou and watch the rest of the team (Kristy, @lee_b48 & @sonnycook82) tag out on some amazing bulls too! We even got to fry up the heart back at camp. Was a different experience being off-grid for the week on a DIY drop hunt of a lifetime! Can’t thank y’all enough!
-
Knife: @coldsteelknives 🔪
Ammo: @federalpremium
